fields.value: Type A Self Report Inventory (CAPS-TYPEASR CAPS-SELF_DESCR and CAPS-SELF_DESCR_PAPER module)

dsDescriptionValue.value:
The Type A Self Report Inventory (TYPEASR) is a 38 item scale (derived from Gough's Adjective Check List) which distinguishes Type A individuals (those with coronary prone behavior) from Type B individuals. Respondents answer on a 7-point scale, indicating how true the adjective displayed is of them.

The Type A Self Report Inventory also correlates with another self report Type A measure, the Jenkins Activity Scale. However, the Type A Inventory, like other Type A measures has not prove n to identify individuals with angiographically determined coronary artery disease. Despite this tendency to misclassify individuals, the measure is a valuable tool for mass screening to identify those at risk for coronary events.

The unit was called SELF_DESCR in CAPS/84. In CAPS/84 the unit was also administered in paper and pencil version.

See codebook for additional information

publicationCitation.value: Blumenthal, James et al. 'Development of a Brief Self-Report Measure of the Type A (Coronary Prone) Behavior Pattern.' Journal of Psychosomatic Research
